#cottage

(room *)
(singleton *)
(name *)	cottage
(look *)

    (par) A spartan, yet somehow cozy cottage, despite the Scandi-style
    furnishings.

    (par) There is a table in the center of the room.

(from * go #east to #front-porch)
(from * go #west to #back-porch)

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

#table

(name *)	table
(singleton *)
(* is #in #cottage)

(descr *)

    A table. Spartan. Not much else can be said about it.

    (if) (#lantern is #on #table) (then)

        (par) There is a candle lantern in the center of the table.

    (endif)

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

(global variable (lantern switch on count 0))

(inc lantern)
    (lantern switch on count $Count)
    ($Count plus 1 into $NewCount)
    (now) (lantern switch on count $NewCount)

(lanter is dead)
    (lantern switch on count 4)

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

#lantern

(item *)
(switchable *)
(name *)	red metal candle lantern
(dict *)	white candle
(heads *)	metal candle lantern
(descr *)

    It's a metal candle lantern. The metal is painted red and shaped
    into a box that holds a white pillar candle.  This candle is not
    much of a pillar anymore though: there's hardly any wax or wick
    left.

(appearance *)

    You notice the candle lantern was left here.

(* is #on #table)

(after [switch on #lantern])
    (inc lantern)

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

#front-porch

(room *)
(name *)	front porch
(look *)	The front porch faces east where your car is parked.

(from * go #west to #cottage)

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

#back-porch

(room *)
(name *)	back porch
(look *)

    The back porch faces west where the forbidden forest is.  The
    inside of the cottage is east.

(from * go #east to #cottage)
(from * go #west to #forest)

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

#forest

(room *)
(singleton *)
(name *)	forbidden forest
(look *)

    The forest is its own microclimate under the canopy of trees.
    It's darker, more humid, breezy, and nature-noisy.

(from * go #east to #porch)

